import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    
    plt.hist(data['delay'], bins=30, color='blue', alpha=0.7, edgecolor='black')
    plt.axvline(data['delay'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Median: {data['delay'].median():.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Delay Time')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of delay time?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    avg_distance = data['distance'].mean()
    plt.bar(['Average Distance'], [avg_distance], color='blue')
    plt.axhline(avg_distance, color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Average Distance: {avg_distance:.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the average distance traveled by flights?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    origin_counts = data['origin'].value_counts()
    destination_counts = data['destination'].value_counts()

    fig, ax = plt.subplots(2, 1, figsize=(10, 8))
    
    origin_counts.plot(kind='bar', ax=ax[0], color='blue', alpha=0.5)
    ax[0].set_title('Most Common Origin Airports')
    ax[0].set_xlabel('Origin')
    ax[0].set_ylabel('Count')
    
    destination_counts.plot(kind='bar', ax=ax[1], color='green', alpha=0.5)
    ax[1].set_title('Most Common Destination Airports')
    ax[1].set_xlabel('Destination')
    ax[1].set_ylabel('Count')
    
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.suptitle('What is the most common origin and destination?', y=1.05, fontsize=14, wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.scatter(data['distance'], data['delay'])
    plt.xlabel('Distance')
    plt.ylabel('Delay')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between delay time and distance?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    
    flights_by_date = data.groupby('date').size()
    
    plt.plot(flights_by_date.index, flights_by_date.values, label='Flights')
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('Number of Flights')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flights by date?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
